>Bonding With Your Pets</b><br>With the busy lives we lead, it can be difficult to spend as much time as one would like to with our pets. Grooming can be used as a bonding opportunity to ensure you and your pets are getting to spend as much quality time together as possible.<br><br><b>Cut Down On Expenses</b><br>Let’s be honest—professional groomers can be pricey! Grooming at home as opposed to frequently visiting a groomer will help to reduce expenses.<br><br><b>Reduced Shedding</b><br>Brushing your pets every day can help to prevent broken and loose hair from falling later! It also prepares the coat for healthy growth which reduces the chance of developing mats and future skin issues.<br></p><!--EndFragment--></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Image" id="e-1593091937389" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1593091937389"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2204/0799/files/Dog-Cat-Furbliss-Brush-01019854.jpg?v=1593016762" alt="Gooming your pets at home" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en"></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Heading" id="e-1593092009957" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1593092009957"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3>Safety While Grooming Your Pet</h3></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Text Block" id="e-1593092030363" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1593092030363"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left" data-gemlang="en"><p>Safety first! Here are some tips on safety precautions to take while grooming your pets.</p></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Icon List" id="m-1593092056138" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-iconlist" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1593092056138"><div class="module gf_module-center gf_module-center-lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs "><ul class="gf_icon-list"><li style="margin-bottom: 15px"><span class="gf-il-icon item-content" data-index="1" data-key="content" style="width: 45px"><div data-label="Icon" id="e-1593092056138-1" class="element-wrap" data-id="1593092056138-1" data-icon="gpicon-icon" data-ver="1.0"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><div class="gf_icon-wrap" style="font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><i class="gf_icon fa fa-paw"></i></div></div></div></span><div class="gf-il-content item-content" data-index="1" data-key="content1" style="padding-left: 45px"><div data-label="Text Block" id="e-1593092056138-2" class="element-wrap" data-id="1593092056138-2" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left"><p style="text-align: inherit!important;">Avoid using scissors, metal brushes, or anything that could (if misused) potentially harm your pet</p></div></div></div></li><li style="margin-bottom: 15px"><span class="gf-il-icon item-content" data-index="2" data-key="content" style="width: 45px"><div data-label="Icon" id="e-1593092056138-3" class="element-wrap" data-id="1593092056138-3" data-icon="gpicon-icon" data-ver="1.0"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><div class="gf_icon-wrap" style="font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><i class="gf_icon fa fa-paw"></i></div></div></div></span><div class="gf-il-content item-content" data-index="2" data-key="content1" style="padding-left: 45px"><div data-label="Text Block" id="e-1593092056138-4" class="element-wrap" data-id="1593092056138-4" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left"><p style="text-align: inherit!important;">Avoid grooming on high surfaces</p></div></div></div></li><li style="margin-bottom: 15px"><span class="gf-il-icon item-content" data-index="3" data-key="content" style="width: 45px"><div data-label="Icon" id="e-1593092056138-5" class="element-wrap" data-id="1593092056138-5" data-icon="gpicon-icon" data-ver="1.0"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><div class="gf_icon-wrap" style="font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><i class="gf_icon fa fa-paw"></i></div></div></div></span><div class="gf-il-content item-content" data-index="3" data-key="content1" style="padding-left: 45px"><div data-label="Text Block" id="e-1593092056138-6" class="element-wrap" data-id="1593092056138-6" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left">Do not leave pets unattended in the tub or on a high surface.</div></div></div></li><li style="margin-bottom: 15px"><span class="gf-il-icon item-content" data-index="4" data-key="content" style="width: 45px"><div data-label="Icon" id="e-1593092224163" class="element-wrap" data-id="1593092224163" data-icon="gpicon-icon" data-ver="1.0"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><div class="gf_icon-wrap" style="font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><i class="gf_icon fa fa-paw"></i></div></div></div></span><div class="gf-il-content item-content" data-index="4" data-key="content1" style="padding-left: 45px"><div data-label="Text Block" id="e-1593092224180" class="element-wrap" data-id="1593092224180" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left"><p style="text-align: inherit!important;">Keep your pets on a leash while grooming to ensure they do not run away</p></div></div></div></li><li style="margin-bottom: 15px"><span class="gf-il-icon item-content" data-index="5" data-key="content" style="width: 45px"><div data-label="Icon" id="e-1593092223149" class="element-wrap" data-id="1593092223149" data-icon="gpicon-icon" data-ver="1.0"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><div class="gf_icon-wrap" style="font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><i class="gf_icon fa fa-paw"></i></div></div></div></span><div class="gf-il-content item-content" data-index="5" data-key="content1" style="padding-left: 45px"><div data-label="Text Block" id="e-1593092223215" class="element-wrap" data-id="1593092223215" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left"><p style="text-align: inherit!important;">Always exercise caution when washing or grooming near your pet’s eyes, ears, or other sensitive areas</p></div></div></div></li><li style="margin-bottom: 15px"><span class="gf-il-icon item-content" data-index="6" data-key="content" style="width: 45px"><div data-label="Icon" id="e-1593092259718" class="element-wrap" data-id="1593092259718" data-icon="gpicon-icon" data-ver="1.0"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><div class="gf_icon-wrap" style="font-size: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><i class="gf_icon fa fa-paw"></i></div></div></div></span><div class="gf-il-content item-content" data-index="6" data-key="content1" style="padding-left: 45px"><div data-label="Text Block" id="e-1593092259646" class="element-wrap" data-id="1593092259646" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left"><p style="text-align: inherit!important;">Remember to always be gentle and keep your grooming equipment clean</p></div></div></div></li></ul></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Heading" id="e-1593092355669" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1593092355669"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3>Grooming to Maintain a Healthy Skin &amp; Coat</h3></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Text Block" id="e-1593092395746" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1593092395746"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left" data-gemlang="en"><p>Pets depend on their humans to maintain their grooming requirements and help keep them looking and feeling their best!<br><br><b>Avoiding infections</b><br>A quick brushing is a great way to make an all-over check to be sure there is nothing that needs veterinary attention, such as lumps, bumps, or skin problems!<br><br><b>Rinsing Allergic Contaminants Off Skin</b><br>Pets can up pick pollutants while outside—pollen, dust, fleas, and ticks can all hitch a ride on your pet and end up in your house. They can also cause allergic reactions in some pets, resulting in itching and hair loss. Regularly grooming your pet will help support a healthy coat and healthy skin!<br><br><b>Exfoliating &amp; DeShedding</b><br>Exfoliation has many benefits, including stimulation of oxygen-rich blood to feed and nourish the skin's surface, detoxification, and helping to remove toxins along with other unhealthy debris. By regularly brushing your pets you are helping them rid of dead skin cells and excess hair which in time will help to reduce your pet’s overall shedding and leave your pet’s coat healthy and shining! We have all heard the saying “look good, feel good”– this saying applies to pets too! A clean pet is indeed a happy pet.</p></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Image" id="e-1593106157896" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1593106157896"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2204/0799/files/Furbliss-Puppy-in-bath-isolated.jpg?v=1593106649" alt="How to give dog bath at home" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en"></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Heading" id="e-1593092471499" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1593092471499"><div class="elm